    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "OFFICE OF DWIGHT D. EISENHOWER\nCommodore Hotel\nNew York, No Y•\nOctober 16, 1952\nDear Mrs. Bixby:\nThank you so much for the amusing\nlittle brass hat ashtray from Paris\nwhich was hand-delivered to my of-\nfice on my birthday•\nI really\nappreciate your thoughtfulness.\nI have returned to my office today,\nand understand you are on your way\nto Tokyo.\nI suppose you'll go\nthrough Manila en route -- with more\nthan a passing thought to the \"good\nold days.\"\nThose were peaceful\ntimes compared to the present.\nSincerely,\nJupit Diser home.\nMrs. Harold M. Bixby\nc/o Mr. Dallas Sherman\nAoP•0. 925, Box 323\nc/o Postmaster\nSan Francisco\n- 303",
      "AIRMAIL\nOFFICE OF DWIGHT D. EISENHOWER\nRoom 651\nCommodore Hotel\nNew York, N. Y.\nYORK. N.\n2\nOCTIS\n12 PM\nMADISON\n1052\nCHIA NAN\n$9\nTyw div\nMrs. Harold M. Bixby\nc/o Mr. Dallas Sherman\nA.P.O. 925, Box 323\nclo Postmaster\nSan Francisco\n0 303"
    ],
